Right now, 9.6% of the total U.S. population had received at least one shot of a #COVID19 #vaccine (11.9% of the age-eligible population).

And you know what? That's pretty decent progress. Do we wish it was going faster? Of course. But the oldest EUAs are less than 2 months old. https://t.co/SFkZKatFO8
